# Copy this file to `.env`:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# You do NOT need a key. This dive is a fully offline SIMULATOR of a realtime voice
# session — it models audio frames and per-stage latency deterministically so you
# can see turn-taking, barge-in, and the latency budget without a microphone, a
# speaker, or a provider. There is one provider here: mock.
#
# Production realtime voice uses the OpenAI Realtime API (speech-to-speech over
# WebSocket/WebRTC) or a streaming STT->LLM->TTS pipeline — see the README. If you
# wire one up, its API key goes in your OS keychain, not here — see ../SECRETS.md.

PROVIDER=mock
